# Hairspa-Bot Domain Rules & Institutional Memory

## 1. The Fallback Sync Rule (CRITICAL)
- The frontend fallback pricing (`page.tsx`) and the backend fallback pricing (`/api/chat/route.ts` or `promptBuilder.ts`) MUST ALWAYS remain perfectly synchronized (e.g., $28/$10).
- If you alter the default pricing logic on the backend, you must simultaneously update the frontend fallback to prevent state desyncs.

## 2. Quick-Reply Button Resilience
- NEVER use strict string matching (e.g., `text === "exact string"`) to determine if quick-reply buttons should render.
- ALWAYS use `.toLowerCase().includes()` with flexible keywords (e.g., `includes("offer")`, `includes("outlet")`, `includes("time")`) because the LLM will naturally vary its phrasing.

## 3. The Golden Schema (Bot Generation)
- When building features to create new bots, DO NOT hallucinate database schemas.
- Treat the MVP bot document in Firestore as the "Golden Schema." New bots should strictly duplicate this structure, altering only the `botName`, `pricing`, and `merchantId`/`userId`.
